<table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4"><tr bgcolor="#000000"><td><font color="#FFFFFF"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial" size="6">Out of Site</font></td></tr></table><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td></td><td>&nbsp;</td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Author</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Big Yoda</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Description</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">A beginners deck for standard. This deck not only has no rares it really needs no rares. It is very, very strong and can place in a tournament with good play.</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Cards</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">Starting<br />
Frodo, RA<br />
The One Ring, tRR<br />
Sam, SoH<br />
Merry, FotB<br />
Pippen, FtF<br />
Smeagol, ON*<br />
<br />
Adventure Deck<br />
[1] The Riddermark<br />
[2] Uruk Camp (Battleground)<br />
[3] Barrows of Edoras<br />
[4] White Rocks (Battleground)<br />
[5] Hornburg Courtyard (Battleground)<br />
[6] Caves of Aglarond<br />
[7] Hornburn Causeway (Battleground)<br />
[8] Nan Curunir<br />
[9] Fortress of Orthanc (Battleground)<br />
<br />
Free Peoples (31)<br />
Aragorn, HoE x2<br />
